50|$|A Murphy drip is a rectal {{infusion}} apparatus {{to administer}} the medical procedure of proctoclysis, also known as <b>rectoclysis.</b> During the procedure, an end of the Murphy drip is inserted into the rectum and large quantities of liquid are infused into the rectum drop by drop. Prior to fluids or medicines being given intravenously, the Murphy drip and hypodermoclysis were the prime routes to administer fluids such as for replacement when patients could not be fed by mouth. Wisconsin surgeon John Benjamin Murphy introduced the drip method of saline infusion per rectum {{in the treatment of}} peritonitis.|$|E

